rfectly useless manner, you have learned how to live\n\n- Lin\n|\nMeasured with magnetic field meters, the electromagnetic field that the heart produces is some 5,000 times more powerful than that created by the brain.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nTake the time to celebrate stillness and silence and see the joy that the world can bring, simply.\n\n- Tony Curl, Seriously Simple Stuff to Get You Unstuck\n|\nPay attention… How a person handles poor cell service, traffic, and spotty wifi is a good indicator of how they’ll behave during relationship challenges.\n\n- Steve\n|\nNever give a sucker an even break, but don't cheat a friend.\n\n- Cary\n|\nGrief embraced him and welcomed him back, showering tears upon his arrival.\n\n- Faraaz\n|\nIf you want to give yourself a fair chance to succeed, never expect too much too soon\n\n- Po\n|\nNever allow your present situation deprive you from your happiness'.\n\n- Abdulazeez\n|\nIt isn't for the moment you are struck that you need courage, but for that long uphill climb back to sanity and faith and security.\n\n- Anne\n|\nWhile humans play God, dogs learn from their masters.\n\n- Toba Beta, Master of Stupidity\n|\nWhen we are no longer able to change a situation, we are challenged to change ourselves.\n\n- Viktor E. Frankl, Man's Search for Meaning\n|\nLearn, only to live. Live, only to learn.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nIt’s all about that cosy, homey feeling, the one you leave behind when you travel across the world.\n\n- Danielle Esplin, Give It Back\n|\nWithout being an independent individual, without having an independent mind, you become nothing more than a trivial slave or an obscure shadow!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nThe Lord will deliver us from every chain of sin, slavery and bondage.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nWe invent what we need to get us by, but in doing so we are really continuing to hold on to the pain of yesterday.\n\n- Stephen Richards, The Pain You Feel Today Is The Strength You Feel Tomorrow\n|\nBe kind to all an